        <briefdescription>
<para>This enum defines the <ref refid="classMR_1a69c80bb31266546933db0c88875afc59" kindref="member">MR.cutMesh</ref> behaviour in case of bad faces acure basicaly <ref refid="classMR_1a69c80bb31266546933db0c88875afc59" kindref="member">MR.cutMesh</ref> removes all faces which contours pass through, adds new edges to topology and fills all removed parts. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para><simplesect kind="note"><para>Bad faces here mean faces where contours have intersections and cannot be cut and filled in an good way </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
